<mxPoint x="-28" y="-10" as="offset" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> <mxCell id="PHtsgstKd2v0GWszpRMV-18" value="<div>ENMODS WR provides the public an ability to search and download data provided by Aquatic Informatics (AQI).&nbsp; Users access the web-based front-end to enter their basic/advanced search criteria.&nbsp; The backend provides a REST API (via NEST), which provides access to the database via TypeORM.</div><div><br></div><div>Every week, AQI posts new data in the form of CSV files in an S3 Bucket.&nbsp; ENMODS WR will check to see if the files are new, and retry several times in case there's a delay in posting the new files.&nbsp; Once it's determined that the new files are posted, AWS CLI is used to stream these files into a staging table.&nbsp; Once the data is completely copied to the staging table, the following occurs: 1. Materialized views are refreshed (which is used to populate dropdown lists on the basic and advanced search screens), 2. the table is indexed.&nbsp; 3. The staging and operational tables are swapped (and the staging table is truncated to prepare for the next week's set of data).</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=#666666;fillColor=#f5f5f5;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontColor=#333333;glass=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="560" width="270" height="330" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="PHtsgstKd2v0GWszpRMV-19" value="<div>WR also pushes monitoring location groups to DataBC.&nbsp; Geodatabase (fgdb) and georeferenced .csv files are migrated from&nbsp;&nbsp;EnMoDS WR to the BC Data Catalogue nightly by posting these files to a bucket in Objecstore.&nbsp; The files are public and can be downloaded without authenticating.</div><div><br></div>" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=#666666;fillColor=#f5f5f5;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontColor=#333333;glass=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="294" y="560" width="240" height="270" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

div.div: ENMODS WR provides the public an ability to search and download data provided by Aquatic Informatics (AQI). Users access the web-based front-end to enter their basic/advanced search criteria. The backend provides a REST API (via NEST), which provides access to the database via TypeORM.

Every week, AQI posts new data in the form of CSV files in an S3 Bucket. ENMODS WR will check to see if the files are new, and retry several times in case there's a delay in posting the new files. Once it's determined that the new files are posted, AWS CLI is used to stream these files into a staging table. Once the data is completely copied to the staging table, the following occurs: 1. Materialized views are refreshed (which is used to populate dropdown lists on the basic and advanced search screens), 2. the table is indexed. 3. The staging and operational tables are swapped (and the staging table is truncated to prepare for the next week's set of data).

div.div: WR also pushes monitoring location groups to DataBC. Geodatabase (fgdb) and georeferenced .csv files are migrated fromEnMoDS WR to the BC Data Catalogue nightly by posting these files to a bucket in Objecstore. The files are public and can be downloaded without authenticating.
